{
  "texts": [
    "It is based on FastSpeech and composed mainly of two feed-forward Transformer (FFTr) stacks [1].",
    "The first one operates in the resolution of input tokens, the second one in the resolution of the output frames.",
    "Let x = (x 1,..., x n) be the sequence of input lexical units, and y = (y 1,..., y t) be the sequence of target mel-scale spectrogram frames.",
    "The first FFTr stack produces the hidden representation h = FFTr(x).",
    "The hidden representation h is used to make predictions about the duration and average pitch of every character with a 1-D CNNEmbedding FFT Block Pitch Predictor Duration Predictor FFT Block Repeat FC Conv 1D FC Conv 1D Conv 1D MSE Loss MSE Loss N x N x Conv 1D FC Conv 1D MSE LossFig. 1."
  ]
}